If you wanna make an impact every game become a mid main, it is the most game impacting role besides the jungler. The way i play mid is, if i know i win the fight vs the laner i engage as soon as i see an opening and win the fight 90% of the time, if i win i make sure to push the lead and keep punishing that laner and after i've gotten 2-3 kills i push the mid wave and look to either bully top/bottom laners or help my jg invade enemy jg. However if i am not sure whether i win the matchup or not i just play safe and try to setup my jungler to gank lane, if im still unsure if that was a good enough lead i ask for a couple more ganks which if are successful (successful gank doesn't mean getting a kill even if you make the.enemy laner back.that is still a successful gank). Then i roam again to punish more lanes and ultimately win the game. If anything is unclear or you need champ suggestions feel free to dm me or comment.

Knowing when to back has way too many variables for it to be explained in just a single comment but pretty much any time the enemy laner backs and you see their jungler near your lane so you cant take platings or the platings have fallen and you feel like you dont have enough time to fully take tower you just push the wave and back. My best tip that really helped me would be to watch how quickly the enemy laner clears the wave and go off of that and if he is laner and you need to back due to low hp/mana/ you got lots of gold try to do that on a cannon wave. When it comes to being behind on cs, dont look at other lanes look at mid lane and how you compare to their mid laner because in a recent patch they nerfed mid cs so you get less cs now. But if you have more cs than enemy mid then you are doing good. A champion i would recommend learning is yasuo. I know he's become a meme but if you put in the work and learn to play him the benefit is huge. For me he is one of the easiest ad champs to farm with but if you wanna go ap then i would recommend xerath he has a poky playstyle in early game and in late you just delete everyone with a single e q w combo. If you need any tips/help on playing xerath or yasuo tell me and i will write up some tips for both of them

Yea if you want i can make you a list of tips that i wish i knew when i started playing him, btw yasuo is so worth it i know lots of players hate on him but if you put in the time you can carry almost every game

Ok so for Yasuo: 1. Buy Berzerkers first (i've seen too many people buying zeal first) and then zeal second 2. If you are playing against heavy ap and are losing go for hexdrinker after Zeal but don't upgrade it to maw at least untill you have your Infinity Edge. Preferably buy Zerkers gt;Zeal gt;IE gt;Statikk gt;Maw 3.If you are vs a champion you don't feel comfortable playing against don't force fights untill you have Zerkers and Zeal (Your q cd will be too long without them and it will be a lot harder to win the fight) 4.Don't buy PhantomDancer and Hexdrinker (same passive) 5.Your R is kinda tricky and it took me a long time to realise R will be cast on the knocked up player closest to your cursor (for example there is a 5 man knock up and if your cursor is not in the middle of them you will not R all of them you will R those closest to the cursor) 6. Practice airblades (if someone is knocked up do EQR either on them or on minions/champions close to them) there are lots of videos that explain it better. 7. Don't take every R ( this is so important, I've seen too many players instantly click R as soon as they see someone is knocked up) 8. If u are playing mid ban sylas he is the hardest counter on mid if playing top then ban renekton. 9. If they have very high cc comp go for clense or if you feel like you can't play without ignite buy Mercurial Schimitar (cc is your worst enemy) 10. Don't build the same items every game (try to itemise for their team) 11. Don't dash just because u can (most of the time you will end up going where you didn't mean to) 12. If you are chasing someone and there are enemy minions near them dash on all the minions first save dashing on the champion as a last resort. 13. Don't be afraid to be aggressive if you are wining lane (yasuo can punish anyone if he is fed) 14.
